> Summer called, it wants you to know it's time to get ready for some well-deserved fun in the sun! This hearty, vibrant lunch idea is packed with delicious veggie—baby lettuce, red cabbage, and carrots form a crisp base for supremely satisfying salad. You'll add protein-packed edamame, juicy mandarin orange segments, nutty sesame seeds, and fresh scallion greens for color, texture, and crunch. It's all tossed with a slightly sweet and very savory peanut-sesame dressing that's frankly the star of the show. Summer glow, here we come!

Wash and dry produce. Drain and rinse @chickpeas{1%unit}; thoroughly pat dry with #paper towels{}.

Place @edamame{4%ounce} and chickpeas in a medium #microwave-safe bowl{}; microwave until warm and slightly tender, ~{30-60%seconds}.

Trim and discard root end from @baby lettuce{1%unit}; chop leaves into bite-size pieces. Thinly slice @scallions{2%unit}, separating whites from greens.

In a large #bowl{}, whisk together @peanut butter{1.15%ounce}, @sesame dressing{3%ounce}, and as many @chili flakes{1%tsp} as you like. Add water 1 tsp at a time until dressing reaches a drizzling consistency.

> TIP: Knead peanut butter packet before opening to make whisking easier.

Add lettuce, @shredded red cabbage{4%ounce}, @shredded carrots{4%ounce}, and scallion whites; toss to coat. Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Divide salad between #bowls{}. Top with edamame and chickpeas, @sesame seeds{1%tbsp}, and scallion greens. Serve.